text.section:
The board may revoke, suspend, or refuse to issue or renew; impose probationary or supervisory conditions upon; impose an administrative fine; issue a written reprimand or admonishment; or any combination of actions regarding any applicant, license, or licensee upon proof that the applicant or licensee has:
Committed any act of dishonesty or corruption. If the act constitutes a crime, conviction in a criminal proceeding is not a condition precedent to disciplinary action. Upon conviction of the crime, the judgment and sentence creates a rebuttable presumption at the ensuing disciplinary hearing of the guilt of the applicant or licensee. Conviction includes all instances in which a plea of no contest is the basis of the conviction;
Misrepresented or concealed a material fact in obtaining a license, or in reinstatement thereof;
Committed any unfair, false, misleading, or deceptive act or practice;
Been incompetent or negligent in the practice of social work;
Violated any state statute or administrative regulation governing the practice of social work or any activities undertaken by a social worker;
Failed to comply with an order issued by the board or an assurance of voluntary compliance;
Violated the code of ethical conduct as set forth by the board by promulgation of an administrative regulation;
Been legally declared mentally incompetent;
Aided or abetted another person in falsely procuring or attempting to procure a license; or
Aided or abetted an unlicensed person in the practice of social work.
